{{Quote|I used to bull's-eye womp rats in my T-16 back home. They're not much bigger than two meters.|[[Luke Skywalker]]|<ref name="ANH">{{Film|IV}}</ref>}}
[[File:Ewoks_SWSB.png|thumb|right|The average Ewok was one meter tall.]]
The '''meter''' was an established unit of measurement of length. [[Starfighter]] [[pilot]]s and their [[targeting computer]]s used meters.<ref name="ANH" /> Species like the [[Ewok]]s,<ref name="EncyclopediaE">{{SWE|groups|ewoks|Ewoks}}</ref> the [[Lurmen]],<ref name="EncyclopediaL">{{SWE|groups|lurmen|Lurmen}}</ref> and the [[Jawa]]s all had an average height of one meter,<ref name="EncyclopediaJ">{{SWE|groups|jawas|Jawas}}</ref> while the [[armor]]ed [[Sith Lord]] [[Anakin Skywalker|Darth Vader]] was slightly taller than two meters.<ref name="EncyclopediaDV">{{SWE|characters|darthvader|Darth Vader}}</ref> [[Grav-ball]] was played on a 64-meter grid that was divided into eight octets.<ref name="gridiron">{{SW|url=news/star-wars-rebels-edge-of-the-galaxy-and-the-grav-ball-gridiron|text=''Star Wars Rebels: Edge of the Galaxy'' and the Grav-Ball Gridiron}}</ref> Meters were also divided into [[centimeter]]s and [[millimeter]]s.<ref name="EncyclopediaVE">{{SWE|technology|vocalemulator|vocal emulator}}</ref> For very large scale measurements, 1,000 meters were put together to make one [[kilometer]].<ref name="SWE-Super Star Destroyer">{{SWE|technology|superstardestroyer|Super Star Destroyer}}</ref><ref name="SWE-Admiral Ozzel">{{SWE|characters|admiral-ozzel|Admiral Ozzel}}</ref>

According to [[Lugubrious Mote]], most [[Sentience|sentient]] species in [[the galaxy]] were about the same size, ranging in height between about half a meter to three meters.<ref name="Legends">''[[The Legends of Luke Skywalker]]''</ref>

